---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import FoundingCTA from "../components/FoundingCTA.astro";

const title = "How I Work — Five Principles | Ascend Griffin";
const description =
  "How I work with founders: always buyer-side, no vendor kickbacks, transparent milestones, fixed pricing on every engagement. 5 principles, no surprises.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <Nav />
  <main class="about">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="about-shell">
        <p class="hero-eyebrow">How I work · Ascend Griffin</p>

        <h1 class="hero-h1">
          Five principles, <em>no surprises</em>.
        </h1>

        <p class="hero-lede">
          This is the contract before the contract. Every engagement — Audit, Discovery, Project Support — runs on these five rules. If any of them is a dealbreaker for your situation, better we both know now than after we've signed.
        </p>

        <p class="hero-hint">↓ Expand a section to read more</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="acc-section">
      <div class="about-shell">
        <details class="acc" name="how" id="the-five">
          <summary class="acc-summary">
            <span class="acc-num">01</span>
            <span class="acc-label">Five principles</span>
            <span class="acc-toggle" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="acc-body">
            <h3 class="acc-h">Five things I <em>won't move on</em>.</h3>

            <ol class="modes">
              <li class="mode">
                <span class="mode-letter">01</span>
                <div class="mode-body">
                  <h4>I'm always on your side.</h4>
                  <p>I don't have hidden arrangements with vendors. If I recommend a person or team, it's because they fit your project — not because I gain from it. If interests diverge anywhere, you know about it before any decision gets made.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="mode">
                <span class="mode-letter">02</span>
                <div class="mode-body">
                  <h4>Price is fixed before the work starts.</h4>
                  <p>No hourly billing. The price is fixed and agreed before I begin. If scope changes mid-flight, we re-paper together — no quiet "this will be a bit more."</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="mode">
                <span class="mode-letter">03</span>
                <div class="mode-body">
                  <h4>I never start without discovery.</h4>
                  <p>A 30-minute call comes first, always — including for one-page audits. Without that conversation I can't honestly tell you whether I'm the right read for your situation, or whether you'd benefit. If I'm not the right read, I'll say so on the call and usually point you toward someone who is.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="mode">
                <span class="mode-letter">04</span>
                <div class="mode-body">
                  <h4>I leave a documented trail.</h4>
                  <p>Every recommendation goes in writing. Every decision lands in a note. If next month a co-founder, board member, or new hire asks "what did we agree?" — there's a line you can quote. You shouldn't be the only person holding the project context in their head.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="mode">
                <span class="mode-letter">05</span>
                <div class="mode-body">
                  <h4>I work to the plan, not to the clock.</h4>
                  <p>Work runs against an agreed plan. If it becomes clear mid-engagement that the scope needs to expand and it genuinely adds value — we discuss and expand. Work-for-the-sake-of-work is bad for both of us: reputationally for me, financially for you. I avoid those situations deliberately. A quality result delivered on time is the best reason for the next project or a longer engagement.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="acc" name="how" id="in-practice">
          <summary class="acc-summary">
            <span class="acc-num">02</span>
            <span class="acc-label">What it looks like in practice</span>
            <span class="acc-toggle" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="acc-body">
            <p class="acc-lede">Three concrete things that follow from the principles above — the parts that usually surprise people on the first engagement.</p>

            <p><strong>Conflicts of interest stay on the record.</strong> If I have any relationship — past project, friendship, prior employer — with a vendor under consideration, you'll know about it before the comparison call. Not after. The "by the way" disclosure is exactly the moment to lose trust.</p>

            <p><strong>I'll recommend you not hire me.</strong> Sometimes the right answer is "you don't need an outside read here, you need to talk to your dev team for one hour." I'd rather give you that 15-minute answer for free than charge $1,000 to confirm something you already know.</p>

            <p><strong>Value is in the outcome, not in the artifacts.</strong> Audit reports, discovery briefs, vendor comparison docs — those are the basis decisions get made on and functionality gets shipped from. On their own, they're tools. The end measure of the work is whether the right decision was made and whether what needed to ship actually shipped. The artifacts stay with you as a basis for future calls, but I don't confuse them with the product.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="acc" name="how" id="from-you">
          <summary class="acc-summary">
            <span class="acc-num">03</span>
            <span class="acc-label">What I expect from you</span>
            <span class="acc-toggle" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="acc-body">
            <h3 class="acc-h">What helps us land the best result.</h3>

            <ul class="exclude">
              <li>
                <span class="exclude-mark">→</span>
                <span><strong>Respond quickly.</strong> Delays in replies directly affect quality and pace. If something's getting complicated in messages — let's put a call on the calendar instead of dragging through a thread.</span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="exclude-mark">→</span>
                <span><strong>Share information fully.</strong> Under NDA you can hand over any document or detail you have. The real picture of the project is what unlocks the most value on my end.</span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="exclude-mark">→</span>
                <span><strong>Give context and push back.</strong> Much of what I do is grounded in 8 years of practice. Some of it rests on hypotheses from prior projects I haven't been able to fully verify in your context. When you voice disagreement early or add context about your business specifics — that's the best way to make the result sharper.</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </section>

    <FoundingCTA service="discovery" />
  </main>
  <Footer />

  <script>
    (function () {
      function init() {
        const items = document.querySelectorAll<HTMLDetailsElement>('details[name="how"]');
        if (!items.length) return;
        const STICKY_OFFSET = 88;
        items.forEach((det) => {
          det.addEventListener("toggle", () => {
            if (!det.open) return;
            const summary = det.querySelector("summary");
            if (!summary) return;
            requestAnimationFrame(() => {
              requestAnimationFrame(() => {
                const rect = summary.getBoundingClientRect();
                window.scrollTo({ top: window.scrollY + rect.top - STICKY_OFFSET, behavior: "smooth" });
              });
            });
          });
        });
      }
      if (document.readyState === "loading") {
        document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", init);
      } else {
        init();
      }
    })();
  </script>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about { background: radial-gradient(ellipse at top right, rgba(184, 135, 58, 0.04), transparent 50%), radial-gradient(ellipse at bottom left, rgba(184, 135, 58, 0.03), transparent 40%), var(--bg-0); min-height: 100vh; }
  .about-shell { max-width: 880px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 var(--gutter); }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .about-shell { padding: 0 var(--gutter-sm); } }

  .hero { padding: 96px 0 48px; }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .hero { padding: 56px 0 32px; } }
  .hero-eyebrow { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--accent-pressed); margin: 0 0 24px; font-weight: 600; }
  .hero-h1 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(44px, 6vw, 76px); line-height: 1.02; letter-spacing: -0.03em; color: var(--text-1); margin: 0 0 28px; font-weight: 700; max-width: 16ch; }
  .hero-h1 em { font-style: italic; color: var(--editorial); font-weight: 700; }
  .hero-lede { font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 24px; max-width: 56ch; }
  .hero-hint { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-3); letter-spacing: 0.04em; margin: 0; }

  .acc-section { padding: 16px 0 40px; }
  .acc { border-top: 1px solid var(--border-2); transition: background var(--dur-base) var(--ease); }
  .acc:last-of-type { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-2); }
  .acc[open] { background: var(--bg-1); border-top-color: var(--text-1); }
  .acc[open] + .acc { border-top-color: var(--text-1); }

  .acc-summary { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 56px 1fr 32px; align-items: center; gap: 16px; padding: 24px 0; cursor: pointer; list-style: none; user-select: none; }
  .acc-summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .acc-summary:hover .acc-label { color: var(--accent-pressed); }
  .acc-summary:focus-visible { outline: 2px solid var(--accent); outline-offset: 2px; border-radius: 2px; }

  .acc-num { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 13px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--accent-pressed); letter-spacing: 0.04em; line-height: 1; }
  .acc-label { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(20px, 2.4vw, 26px); color: var(--text-1); line-height: 1.2; letter-spacing: -0.01em; font-weight: 700; transition: color var(--dur-fast) var(--ease); }
  .acc[open] .acc-label { color: var(--editorial); }
  .acc-toggle { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 28px; color: var(--accent-pressed); line-height: 1; text-align: right; transition: transform var(--dur-base) var(--ease); font-weight: 300; }
  .acc[open] .acc-toggle { transform: rotate(45deg); }

  .acc-body { padding: 0 0 36px 72px; max-width: 68ch; }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .acc-body { padding: 0 0 28px 0; } }
  .acc-h { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(22px, 2.6vw, 28px); line-height: 1.2; letter-spacing: -0.015em; color: var(--text-1); margin: 0 0 20px; font-weight: 700; max-width: 24ch; }
  .acc-h em { font-style: italic; color: var(--editorial); }
  .acc-body p { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 18px; }
  .acc-body p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .acc-body p strong { color: var(--text-1); font-weight: 700; }
  .acc-body p em { font-style: italic; color: var(--text-1); }
  .acc-lede { font-size: 17px; color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 28px; }

  .modes { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--border-2); }
  .mode { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 40px 1fr; gap: 20px; padding: 24px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-1); align-items: start; }
  .mode:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
  .mode-letter { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 18px; color: var(--accent-pressed); font-weight: 700; line-height: 1; letter-spacing: -0.01em; }
  .mode-body h4 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 18px; color: var(--text-1); margin: 0 0 8px; line-height: 1.35; font-weight: 700; }
  .mode-body p { font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text-2); margin: 0; max-width: 60ch; }

  .exclude { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
  .exclude li { display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 16px; padding: 14px 0; border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--border-1); color: var(--text-2); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.55; }
  .exclude li:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
  .exclude-mark { font-family: var(--font-mono); color: var(--accent-pressed); font-size: 18px; line-height: 1; flex-shrink: 0; font-weight: 700; }
  .exclude strong { color: var(--text-1); font-weight: 700; }
</style>
